Load data

setwd("~/Shrubs-Seedlings/compiled_data/")
load(file="fire_footprints/master_seedlings.Rdata")

Filter to just firs

df <- df[df$Species%in%c("ABCO","ABMA", "PSME") & !df$Fire %in% c("PLKN","FRDS"),]
df <- df %>% filter(!is.na(shrubarea2))

Change species to factor

df <- df %>% 
  mutate(Species = as.factor(Species))
normalize <- function(x) {
    return ((x - mean(x)) / sd(x))
  }

Normalize variables that still need it

df <- df %>% 
  mutate(Cov1.2_norm = normalize(Cov1.2)) %>% 
  mutate(Cov1.3_norm = normalize(Cov1.3)) %>% 
  mutate(shrubarea3_sqrt_norm = normalize(sqrt(shrubarea3)))

Conditional inference tree

See how well random forest predicts data

train = sample(1:nrow(df), nrow(df)/2)
tree_train = randomForest(formula = VertGrowth_Rel ~ Fire + Year + Species + Ht_cm + shrubarea2 + shrubarea3 + Cov1 + Cov1.2 + Cov1.3 + Ht1 + Ht1.2 + Ht1.3 + ShrubSpp01 + ShrubSpp02 + ShrubSpp03 + IAG, 
                    data = df,
                    importance = TRUE,
                    mtry = 13,
                    subset = train)
yhat.bag = predict(tree_train, newdata = df[-train,])
growth.test = unlist(df[-train, "VertGrowth_Rel"])
plot(yhat.bag, growth.test)
abline(0,1)

save(df, file ="~/../Documents/Shrubs-Seedlings/compiled_data/fire_footprints/fir_vert.Rdata")

Initial look at regression model

f <- VertGrowth_Rel ~  Year + shrubarea2_sqrt_norm + Ht_norm + ShrG1 + shrubarea2_sqrt_norm*Ht_norm + Species
f_noshrubs <- VertGrowth_Rel ~  Year + Ht_norm  + ShrG1 + Species
LM1 <- lme(f,data = df, random = list(~ 1| Fire, ~1| Sdlg), method = "ML")
LM1_noshrubs <- lme(f_noshrubs,data = df, random = list(~ 1| Fire, ~1| Sdlg), method = "ML")
anova(LM1, LM1_noshrubs)
##              Model df       AIC       BIC   logLik   Test  L.Ratio p-value
## LM1              1 14 -995.1896 -941.2588 511.5948                        
## LM1_noshrubs     2 12 -997.2442 -951.0178 510.6221 1 vs 2 1.945424  0.3781

Find all possible variable combinations

v1 <- c("shrubarea2_sqrt_norm", "Cov1.2_norm" , "Cov1.3_norm" , "IAG", "ShrG1", "shrubarea2_sqrt_norm*Ht_norm", "shrubarea3_sqrt_norm")
combs <- do.call("c", lapply(seq_along(v1), function(i) combn(v1, i, FUN = list)))
list.bad <- list()
for(i in 1:length(combs)){
  if("Cov1.2_norm" %in% combs[i][[1]] & "Cov1.3_norm" %in% combs[i][[1]])
    {
    list.bad <- c(list.bad, i)
    }
  if("shrubarea2_sqrt_norm" %in% combs[i][[1]] & ("Cov1.2_norm" %in% combs[i][[1]] | "Cov1.3_norm" %in% combs[i][[1]]     )){
    list.bad <- c(list.bad, i)
  } 
    if("shrubarea3_sqrt_norm" %in% combs[i][[1]] & "shrubarea2_sqrt_norm" %in% combs[i][[1]])
    {
    list.bad <- c(list.bad, i)
    }
}
list.bad <- unlist(list.bad)
combs.bad <- combs[list.bad]
combs <- setdiff(combs, combs.bad)
length(combs)
## [1] 55

Table

table <- data.frame(Model = character(), Formula = character(), AIC = numeric())
for(i in 1:length(combs)){
  vars <- combs[i]
  vars <- paste(vars[[1]], collapse="+")
  f <- formula(paste("(VertGrowth_Rel ~  Year  + Ht_norm +", vars,")"))
  M <- lme(f,data = df, random = list(~ 1| Fire, ~1| Sdlg), method = "REML", weights = varExp(form=~Ht_norm))
  ModelName <- paste("M", i, sep="_")
  add <- data.frame(c(ModelName),c(vars), c(AIC(M)))
  table <- rbind(table, add)
}
colnames(table) <- c("Model","Variables", "AIC")
table_final <- kable(table %>% arrange(AIC), format = "markdown")

Compare best model to null

AIC model selection shows that this is the best model, when year and height are included:

f <- VertGrowth_Rel ~  Year + shrubarea2_sqrt_norm + Ht_norm 
f_null <- VertGrowth_Rel ~  Year + Ht_norm 
LM2 <- lme(f,
           data = df, 
           random = list(~ 1| Fire, ~1| Sdlg), 
           method = "ML",
           weights = varExp(form=~Ht_norm))
LM2_null <- lme(f_null,
                data = df, 
                random = list(~ 1| Fire, ~1| Sdlg),
                method = "ML",
                weights = varExp(form=~Ht_norm))
anova(LM2, LM2_null)
##          Model df       AIC       BIC   logLik   Test   L.Ratio p-value
## LM2          1  9 -1018.408 -983.7382 518.2040                         
## LM2_null     2  8 -1020.170 -989.3522 518.0849 1 vs 2 0.2382677  0.6255

Plot

Create MyData

MyData <-  rbind(
  expand.grid( 
    Fire = unique(df$Fire), 
    Year = unique(df$Year), 
    shrubarea2 = seq(min(df$shrubarea2), max(df$shrubarea2), length = 100),
    #shrubarea3 = seq(min(df$shrubarea3), max(df$shrubarea3), length = 100),
    Ht_cm = seq(min(df$Ht_cm), max(df$Ht_cm), length = 10),
    Species = c("PIPO","PILA"),
    ShrG1 = unique(df$ShrG1),
    Cov1.2 = seq(min(df$Cov1.2), max(df$Cov1.2), length = 10)
    )
)

Normalize MyData variables

MyData <- MyData %>% 
  mutate(Ht_norm = normalize(Ht_cm)) %>% 
  mutate(shrubarea2_sqrt_norm = normalize(sqrt(shrubarea2)) ) %>% 
  mutate(cov1.2_norm = normalize(Cov1.2)) 
#%>% 
 # mutate(shrubarea3_sqrt_norm = normalize(sqrt(shrubarea3)))
MyData$pred_simple <- predict(LM2, level = 0,newdata = MyData)

Summary plot

MyData_summary_simple <- MyData %>% 
  group_by(shrubarea2) %>% 
  mutate(pred_simple = mean(pred_simple))
